On va changer nos labels en 0 et 1, pour que ce soit plus facilement utilisable dans le rseau de neurones

In [143]:
for i in range(0,len(df["label"])):
    if df["label"][i] == "__label__1 ":
        df["label"][i] = 0
    else:
        df["label"][i] = 1

In [154]:
ps = PorterStemmer()
corpus = []
for i in range(0,len(df["text"])):
    sentence = re.sub('[^a-zA-Z]', ' ', df["text"][i])
    sentence = sentence.lower()
    sentence = sentence.split()
    
    sentence = [ps.stem(word) for word in sentence if not word in stopwords.words("english")]
    sentence = ' '.join(sentence)
    corpus.append(sentence)

Model¶

In [162]:
embedding_vector_features = 40 #dimension/number of features
model = Sequential()
model.add(Embedding(voc_size, embedding_vector_features, input_length = sent_length))
model.add(LSTM(100))
model.add(Dense(1, activation='sigmoid'))
model.compile(loss='binary_crossentropy', optimizer='adam', metrics=['accuracy'])
model.summary()

In [163]:
from keras.layers import Flatten
from keras.layers import Dropout
from keras.layers.convolutional import Conv1D
from keras.layers.convolutional import MaxPooling1D
In [191]:
model2 = Sequential()
model2.add(Embedding(voc_size, embedding_vector_features, input_length = sent_length))
model2.add(Conv1D(filters=64, kernel_size=3, activation='relu'))
model2.add(Dropout(0.25))
model2.add(MaxPooling1D(pool_size=2))
model2.add(Flatten())
model2.add(Dense(1, activation='sigmoid'))
model2.compile(loss='binary_crossentropy', optimizer='adam', metrics=['accuracy'])
model2.summary()
